International Brief -- San Paolo Holding S.p.A.:
   Bank Plans Public Offering
   To Sell 125 Million Shares
The offering, which has been guaranteed by an
international syndicate coordinated by Milan merchant bank
Mediobanca S.p.A., will raise 1.525 trillion ($1.22 billion)
lire in fresh funds for the bank.
   San Paolo, based in Turin, is currently owned by San Paolo
Holding S.p.A., whose stake will be diluted to around 80%
after the offering. The bank has more than 800 branches, 78
trillion lire in customer loans, and controls 7.8% of the
Italian market.